## Solution A – Parameter Reduction Techniques Employed Within "Eve" Module Architecture :







### Proposed Modifications **:





#### **a). Squeeze Operators *:﻿​This approach involves replacing traditional MP operations like max pooling or minpooling kernels ("Squeeze") directly after each convolution layer instead employing separate dedicated squeeze operators.** Although squeezing introduces additional computations due its iterative nature compared conventional MAX pool implementations, it achieves significant reduction factor (~80% ) WITHOUT compromising fidelity. Squeezing is particularly advantageous because unlike other techniques that discard information from previous stages such pruning which reduces overall network capacity considerably,. With squeezed channels one obtains richer representations leading potentially improved downstream tasks performances than pruned networks despite increased computational cost associated wtih executing multiple iterations over entire feature maps during training process.​






##### b)** Quantization*: quantization converts high precision weights into lower ones thereby shrinking memory footprint drastically at expense sacrificing some dynamic range capabilities.(e g., converting FPFP values ​​into INT types ). Applying quantized versions optimized architectures achieve substantial reductions ranging between ~79%-~ машин depending upon chosen truncation schemes employed ​during optimization processes.<br>However quantification often leads undesirable artifacts introduced via nonlinearities inherent deep learning frameworks limiting effectiveness especially if implemented improperly hence careful implementation strategies must devised meticulously balancing compression gains against detrimental impacts arising out inaccurate approximations.***

